Diagnosis: P 4 with distally positioned postprotocrista. P 4 metacone slightly smaller than paracone. P 4 protocone recurvature minor. P 4 with metaconid and short talonid basin. P 4 and molar exodaenodonty moderate. Buccal cusps of molars not high crowned, so buccal and lingual cusps are widely spaced. Entoconulid strong on M 1 , weak to absent on M 2 (shared with
Te. brisswalteri
).
